Financial incentives are reductions in cost given companies in order to elicit a certain action.
Wassall and Hellman ‘85
- Gregory (Associate Professor and Graduate Coordinator Economics Northeastern University), - Daryl A. (Noted author in the field of economics ie: ‘The Economic Crime’, ‘State financial incentives to industry’), Policy Studies Review; May85, Vol. 4 Issue 4, p626-639, 14p
Financial incentive include cash, credit and/or a reduction in the cost of doing business offered by the government or a public agency to a firm who, in turn, agrees to place or expand a facility in a location designated by the government agency. Within this context, incentives take many forms and dimensions

