Whenever an individual controls the dimensions of&amp;#34; a problem, he or she can solve the problem through a personal decision. For example, if the problem is whether to go to the basketball game tonight, if tickets are not too expensive and if transportation is available, the decision can be made individually. But if a friend~’s car is needed to get to the game, then that person~’s decision to furnish the transportation must be obtained.
